(On the surface, that sounded normal—trial conversion rates in SaaS average 10-25%. But the Bloom team knew something was off. Their product had excellent retention for *paid* users. The problem wasn't the product. It was that most trial users never actually *used* the product deeply enough to fall in love with it.) Tj
ET
